mwyiT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Some of you have asked how Chessie and Puddles are doing with Frank. Well....</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/YU5tNBu.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>There are bad days</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ETx4XQZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>And there are good days.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Bd355h4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Honestly, Puddles is really chill with Frank and actually tried to groom Frank for a little bit. Frank was not okay with that though. But sitting near each other is okay.

Chessie is going to take some time to warm up to him. That's okay. It's only been five days.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/NgqTpnw.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Frank is Frank.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/8bi2hIv.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Bonus video. @KittensForDays reminded me that I have a Ring setup in my house as well. Here's Frank having a blast bouncing off the furniture.

Going to see Superman tonight. It should be good, I've heard good things about it.

Hope your Thursday evening is going well.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DXo9ibt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[FrankTheKitten]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Sometimes People And Kittens Grow Up – Inseparable</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/p4gup0Z</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1fS32aZ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>(Source) Alina / merletails: "The way he grew out of the hand carry breaks my heart."
